What I Learned

Working on this Windows Hardening Script helped me develop practical cybersecurity and IT skills, including:

1. PowerShell Scripting

Learned to automate system administration tasks using PowerShell.

Practiced loops, conditional logic, error handling (try/catch), and output formatting.


2. Virtual Macine Use

Downloaded VirtualBox hosted hypervisor

Created a VDI and installed Windows ISO

Took Snaps shots and transferred script to the VM

Ran the script in the VM

3. Windows Security Hardening

Gained hands-on understanding of hardening endpoints.

Explored key security controls like:

Disabling legacy protocols (SMBv1)

Enabling firewall profiles

Disabling unnecessary or risky services

Enforcing strong password policies

Managing user accounts like Guest

4. Defensive Security Awareness

Learned how small configuration changes reduce the attack surface.

Developed awareness of common vulnerabilities in Windows systems.

5. Reporting and Documentation

Created structured output (software inventory) for auditing purposes.

Learned how to clearly document scripts and instructions for others to follow.

6. Portfolio and Professional Skills

Practiced writing a professional, GitHub-ready project for cybersecurity portfolios.

Learned how to explain technical work clearly to recruiters or hiring managers.
